race.comment: ZANJEER (3) is a progressive type who led throughout fresh at Ballina and put a space on his rivals to score. Fitter and looks well placed here with the claim. Tricky gate but will go forward and take catching again. TRISKELION (2) looks a danger. Resumed here at first try on new home track and drifted back but found the line nicely to place. Fitter again and will be winding up late. HIT (9) struggled here on the Poly track two back then back to the turf on the Sunshine Coast last time gave a sight when placed and beaten less than a length. Goes well here and will give a sight despite the draw. RIVA D'AMOR (8) wound up strongly to score on the Sunshine Coast latest. Has the claim and will be finishing on hard again. VORKUTA (4) was a maiden winner at Toowoomba before a break in a hot form race. Fitter for three trials and has the claim and a low draw.
